🚀 Docker Starter Guide (Structured)
1️⃣ Basic Docker Commands
📌 Check Docker
docker --version
📌 Pull Image
docker pull ubuntu
📌 Run Container
docker run -it ubuntu bash
📌 List Containers
docker ps      # running
docker ps -a   # all
📌 Stop & Remove
docker stop <container_id>
docker rm <container_id>
📌 Images
docker images
docker rmi <image_id>
2️⃣ Project: Node.js Docker App
📁 Folder Structure
docker-demo/
│── app.js
│── package.json
│── Dockerfile
│── .dockerignore
📄 app.js
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
    res.end("Hello Ram 🚀 Docker is working!");
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
    console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
📄 package.json
{
  "name": "docker-demo",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "app.js",
  "dependencies": {}
}
📄 Dockerfile
FROM node:18

WORKDIR /app

COPY . .

RUN npm install

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["node", "app.js"]
📄 .dockerignore
node_modules
npm-debug.log
3️⃣ Build & Run
🔨 Build Image
docker build -t docker-demo .
▶️ Run Container
docker run -p 3000:3000 docker-demo
🌐 Output
http://localhost:3000